<br>
 Just outside Ssra temple is a good place for fear kiting. Along west side of temple there's a pathing bug that makes feared mobs pace back and forth. <br>
<br>
I have ROTWF, fungi, Tq staff, COCW for gear. <br>
<br>
Bring bandages, lots ).<br>
<br>
Is sweet for a duo with necro, druid, cleric, ranger or pretty much any other duo ). <br>
<br>
If Instill Doubt is maxxed then you will have minimal problems. At lvl 58 soloing snakes was hard if ID didn't land, some i could chain fear others couldn't stick it for the life of me.<br>
<br>
59 i can sometimes toe to toe the snakes....but they stand no chance if i get id off. <br>
<br>
Is a favorite place for druids and wizards to quad kite. Just let them know the reason of using back wall of temple and they usually have np if you take golems and snakes near front of temple.<br>
<br>
Named snakes are not fearable....agro kite with a druid or necro...they have sow speed so make sure they don't slow down ). <br>
<br>
Golems drop cash, snakes drop gems worth around 12ppish. Named snakes drop good twink gear and an eb earring (rare) with ac and some stats....which i'm still waiting for. named golems drop twink gear too.<br>
<br>
Undead oragans are for a neckpiece eb device with hp and mana stats if i recall correctly, starting in Katta. 3 needed.<br>
<br>
That's all for now ) happy hunting!<br>
